item.title: CVE-2022-3836|2024-08-03T01:20:58.299Z -- unknown -- seed%20social
item.description: The Seed Social WordPress plugin before 2.0.4 does not sanitise and escape some of its settings, which could allow high privilege users such as admin to perform Stored Cross-Site Scripting attacks even when the unfiltered_html capability is disallowed (for example in multisite setup).
